          <title>PROGRESS NOTES</title>
          <text>
            <table xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
              <thead><tr><th>Date</th><th>Provider</th><th>Note Type</th><th>Note Text</th><th>Location</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr><td>03/15/2026</td><td>Cory Denton, FNP</td><td>Progress Note</td><td>CC: RA follow-up, biologics monitoring.
HPI: 50yo female with seropositive RA (RF+, CCP+) on adalimumab + leflunomide. Recovered from flare Nov 2025 -- added short burst prednisone, now tapered to 5mg maintenance. Current DAS28: 2.8 (low disease activity). Reports morning stiffness 20 min (was 90 min during flare). Hand grip improved. No injection site reactions with adalimumab.
PE: Hands -- mild MCP synovitis bilateral, improved. No swan-neck deformities. Wrists -- full ROM, no effusion. Knees -- no effusion.
Assessment:
# RA (M06.9): Low disease activity on current regimen. Continue adalimumab q2 weeks + leflunomide.
# Latent TB (R76.11): Completed 4-month rifampin course 2023. No active TB symptoms. Chest XR 2025 stable.
# Osteopenia (M81.8): Chronic prednisone. DEXA due 2026. Continue calcium/D counseling.
# HTN (I10): BP 126/78 on amlodipine. At goal.
# GERD (K21.0): Controlled on omeprazole.
Plan: Continue adalimumab, leflunomide, prednisone 5mg. Taper prednisone to 2.5mg over 4 weeks if stable. Labs q3 months (CBC, CMP, ESR/CRP). Rheumatology annual visit due. DEXA ordered. Return 3 months.</td><td>Family Practice Associates of Chesterfield</td></tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </text>
        </section>
